This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically in the area of urban scene understanding and analysis. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for building extraction and real-time depth estimation from aerial imagery suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of transfer learning and optimization strategies also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on urban environments and building structures suggests that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
